      "message": "[warning] Line 1401: The resolver only scans the first 1024 commits when walking back from a status high-water-mark. A collaborative document can produce more than 1024 consecutive COLLAB_UPDATE commits after the last surfaced message, so the read/fetched pointer would remain unresolved and the regression can reappear for active documents. Please make this walk unbounded or paginate until a non-COLLAB_UPDATE commit or history end is reached.\n\n```suggestion\n            logOptions.nbOfCommits \u003d 0;\n```\n\nIf `0` is not the repository API\u0027s unbounded value, use the existing pagination/walk API instead of a fixed cap.",
